<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by madmike:
[B]I just went into Befallen with my 12 Necro. I've got lots of nice anti-undead spells, so I figured I could breeze the first floor and get into the second. Not so. First the named skelly on the first floor wastes my pet and brings me down to half a bubble of health before I killed him (he was a blue con). My second pet goes wandering off into oblivion thanks to the lousy pathing in Befallen. My third pet attacks and pursues a green con plague rat. I try to get it to back off, but no good. Then I try running, fall off a path and look behind me to see the rat, 3 skellies and a mummy. It was over fast. Don't think I'll be going back there any time soon. And I don't know I'll ever use my Pet in a dungeon again.[/B][/QUOTE]

