<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Macrai</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I was running around WC the other day when I fell into this tunnel entrance in the side of the cliff on the sandy side of WC.  Not knowing what it was I ventured in and low and behold I had found Befallen.  Now being a mighty dwarf Paladin of 9 seasons I figured this to be alittle over my head since was so far from a city.  How wrong I was.  The skeletons proved to be blues and whites with some decaying thrown in.  This was the most fun I've had in many a week of adventuring.  I was even able to defeat the Skeleton Llord with some help from a friendly cleric named, Care.  Once I was able to defeat the lord I considred myself strong enough to defeat the Shadowknight who held the key to the lower reaches of the area.  Got the key and just now am getting prepared to venture deeper.  The undead fear spell the Paladins get at level 9 saved my butt many a times when I was starting to get over whelmed by the constant onslaught of Skeletons(not to mention the trains being brought up from the lower levels).<P>My point is, just because there is no city close by doesn't mean it is a HIGH level dungeon. Take a peek inside. You'll know after the first few mobs you encounter if it is to tough for your level.<P>Kitelar, Paldin on Povar.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Epicurus Quickli</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just watch the lower levels..they grow bigger and more difficult very quickly. The nice chocolate exterior may seem sweet..but trust me..the center is molten steel.Hunt well...<P>------------------<BR>Epi/Brood<BR>GoH of Test<BR>Healin and Barshin Norath daily</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">madmike</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I just went into Befallen with my 12 Necro. I've got lots of nice anti-undead spells, so I figured I could breeze the first floor and get into the second. Not so. First the named skelly on the first floor wastes my pet and brings me down to half a bubble of health before I killed him (he was a blue con). My second pet goes wandering off into oblivion thanks to the lousy pathing in Befallen. My third pet attacks and pursues a green con plague rat. I try to get it to back off, but no good. Then I try running, fall off a path and look behind me to see the rat, 3 skellies and a mummy. It was over fast. Don't think I'll be going back there any time soon. And I don't know I'll ever use my Pet in a dungeon again.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Azhanti</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">No, Mike <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif"> Taking a pet into a dungeon is a dodgy proposition at best, since generally they con a bit weaker than yourself but still aggro the mobs. When they're finished beating on the pet they transfer the aggro to you. If you don't keep a tight rein on your pet and stop it chasing off you'll end up training yourself...not a pleasent experience  <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/frown.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Frenick</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The skeleton is called Llrod and is part of the SK 'reaper of the dead' quest ... NOT the Skeleton Lord ! (good grief). Plus, befallen has just changed in a major way .. DON'T go in there at &lt; lvl 15. You have been warned</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kiiyone</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Was in Befallen last night (7-9-01) and saw that it has reverted to the old-style "easy" version. Apparently there is a trigger that "toggles" between a dark-elf controlled befallen, and the undead befallen.<P>Hung out on the first level and Llrod and I had a little fight. Took me down to half my life before I got him.<P>Kiiyone<BR>Level 15 monk<BR>Karana</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wallice Furyblades</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hey man, by the way, don't get to crazy with that fear undead spell, hehe trust me. It may seem good but if you cast it the mob can run all around the whole dungeon, picking up a few of his buddies from lvl 3 of the dungeon, before returning up to kill you and the rest of the lower lvl people up there. trust me, it happened to me and everyone was REALLY mad about it. Well just thought Id let you know, and By the way, whats up with the dugeon now? i havent been there in some time, is it still low lvl or what? what is the lvl range there now, and is it even Undead still? Thanks a lot<P><BR><P>------------------<BR>Wallice Furyblades<BR>36th Season Paladin<BR>Leader of "Era of Steel" <BR>Terris Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Grubik</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well I was there with my 27 warrior last week. Me, being foolish, thought I could breeze threw this zone and maybe pick up a little loot. There are swarms of greenies that agro like mad. There are some undead but also alot of Dark elves(don't worry they aren't aligned with other dark elf factions if you're evil) they all have necro and shadow night spells and yes, at 27 with almost full crafted I got killed here. I got locked in a room after I chased down a green who ran into a hallway(the door had been opened by someone) I chased him in and the door closed behind me, no one in the zone was able to get the key so I was sittin there waitin for the door to open. What do you know, all the greens that had been killed repopped. I can take on greens no problem, unless those greens have lots of DoT's, fears, and high DD's. This wasn't just one or two little casters this was like 10-15 casters. Damn You Lany's T'vyl!! Its her that caused these changes, no longer is it a happy little undead, even though I wasn't there prior to these things I have heard of people around the level I was at being ok. I have also heard that with the "new" befallen there are more swarming greens that are deadly.<P>Be carefull in there!!!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shingoku</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm a lvl 15 Monk and have been quite literally whooped into shape in the new befallen.  They have root spells which I always seem to get on me and then they all pummel me...or anyone else in the area.  Its not fun to see all these dark elves, their pets and undead kickin' your butt.  Its good for leveling tho...as long as you stick close to the WC zone and don't get too kocky  <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P><BR> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">Originally posted by Grubik:<BR><B>Well I was there with my 27 warrior last week. Me, being foolish, thought I could breeze threw this zone and maybe pick up a little loot. There are swarms of greenies that agro like mad. There are some undead but also alot of Dark elves(don't worry they aren't aligned with other dark elf factions if you're evil) they all have necro and shadow night spells and yes, at 27 with almost full crafted I got killed here. I got locked in a room after I chased down a green who ran into a hallway(the door had been opened by someone) I chased him in and the door closed behind me, no one in the zone was able to get the key so I was sittin there waitin for 